<br>
.:Site Path:. <br>
 [1] Bid as high as you need to get Aragorn out.<br>
 [2] Lotsa Possessions in this deck= lotsa cards drawm<br>
 [3] Fords didnt fit, House of Elrond didnt fit, this is good because twilight removal. <br>
 [4] wound on Gimli is better than burden from Eregion Hills.<br>
 [5] did i have a choice?<br>
 [6] Less wounds to remove in the Fellowship phase<br>
 [7] Low Twilight<br>
 [8] Low twilight and good healing<br>
 [9] 3 trackers plus high twilight = fun<br>
<br>
<br>
.:Free People:.<br>
 Basic objective: Keep Frodo alive. Frodo should not have to fight unless you have a really bad draw. If you haven&#39;t noticed yet, all Aragorn signets except Gimli and Borimir. Don&#39;t be saying &quot;why is he playing that borimir when he should be playing the Aragorn signet?&quot; I will answer that now. You can heal himn for 4 twilight. I play the mines Gimli because I had just traded my Son of Gloin and dwarf of Erebor sucks. Gandalf&#39;s Cart in case Gimli or an Elf dies and you can&#39;t play their possessions. <br>
<br>
.:Shadow:. <br>
 This portion really works in multiplayer where opponent plays beatdown and u make them exert alot and take 4 archery. I won a 4 player game by using Hate on his Legolas when he was exhausted and swarmed his Frodo and Sam. Get you bring on peeps so they cant heal that often. It&#39;s a pretty simple deck.<br>
<br>
